			<h3 ><a href="#p150840">Re: Guild Wars 2, due 2011/2012</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=150840#p150840"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=51" style="color: #AA0000;" class="username-coloured">Nadia</a></strong> &raquo; Feb 15th, '11, 11:45 </p>

			

			<div class="content">GW2 preview at Eurogamer<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/guild-wars-2-preview_4">http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/guild ... -preview_4</a><!-- m --><br /><blockquote class="uncited"><div>Guild Wars 2's switch from an almost entirely instanced game-world, where you would adventure with only your party members, to a persistent, fully-populated one like those in more conventional MMOs, is the driving force behind most of the changes in the gameplay. <br /><br />The quest system, for instance, has been completely overhauled, and will offer something quite different from its competitors. <br /><br />&quot;I think I can safely say that you won't see a single exclamation mark floating above a character's head in Guild Wars 2,&quot; claims lead designer Eric Flannum.</div></blockquote></div>

			

		</div>

		
